						<div class="postbody">I made an equivalent to PCX2CHR in Python, called pilbmp2nes, so that's not quite the problem. (Despite the name, it handles multiple CHR formats.)<br /><br />But the NES has cc65, and at least one game in each of the two volumes of Action 53 so far has been written mostly in C: Zooming Secretary in the first volume and Chase in the second. So is one of the Russian Roulette games coming soon for NES. What tools for C (not assembly language) are in that directory listing? And would a revived x816 handle SPC700 as well?</div>

